{
  "name": "remove-inferred-shot-groups-20260406-1532",
  "idea": "Remove inferred shot groups entirely. Only pinned groups exist on the timeline.\n\n## What to do\n\n1. Strip the inference engine from useShotGroups. The hook should ONLY convert pinnedShotGroups from timeline config into ShotGroup[] for rendering. Remove: per-shot iteration, gap detection, image index ordering, clipGenerationIds map, all the shot.images scanning, finalVideoShotIds parameter, the deduplication logic. The shots parameter is still needed for resolving shot names.\n\n2. Remove isPinned from ShotGroup \u2014 all groups are pinned, the distinction is gone. Remove the dashed/solid border distinction in TimelineCanvas. All groups render with the current pinned styling (thick border, hover for top bar).\n\n3. Remove finalVideoShotIds computation and useFinalVideoAvailable hook from TimelineEditor since the final video badge was tied to inferred groups. The switch-to-video feature now works through pinned groups only (which it already does via useSwitchToFinalVideo).\n\n4. Clean up: remove the debug console.logs from useShotGroups, remove dismissedFinalVideoIds module-level Set, remove the resolveFinalVideoShotIds function from TimelineEditor.\n\n5. Update TimelineCanvas props \u2014 remove finalVideoShotIds. The hasFinalVideo on positioned groups should now be derived from whether the pinned group's shot has a final video (check finalVideoMap inside TimelineEditor when building the shot groups, or pass finalVideoMap and let TimelineCanvas check).\n\nActually wait \u2014 the final video badge (switch to video/images) should still work on pinned groups. It just needs to check finalVideoMap for the group's shotId. This is already wired through the context menu. The only thing to remove is the auto-detection on inferred groups.\n\n6. Update useShotGroups tests \u2014 remove inference tests, keep pinned group tests.\n\nKey files:\n- src/tools/video-editor/hooks/useShotGroups.ts \u2014 gut the inference, keep pinned conversion\n- src/tools/video-editor/hooks/useShotGroups.test.ts \u2014 update tests\n- src/tools/video-editor/components/TimelineEditor/TimelineEditor.tsx \u2014 remove finalVideoShotIds, useFinalVideoAvailable, resolveFinalVideoShotIds, simplify useShotGroups call\n- src/tools/video-editor/components/TimelineEditor/TimelineCanvas.tsx \u2014 remove finalVideoShotIds prop, isPinned distinction, simplify styling\n- src/tools/video-editor/hooks/useFinalVideoAvailable.ts \u2014 delete or keep minimal (just finalVideoMap for the context menu)\n- src/tools/video-editor/components/TimelineEditor/ShotGroupContextMenu.tsx \u2014 simplify (no isPinned checks)",
